%% 08 - STT session lifecycle & resilience (single live session, NO failover)
%% Source: sttService.js + listenService.js. Resilience keeps ONE session healthy;
%% it does not switch models/providers. A mid-session socket drop is logged, not recovered.
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Initializing
    Initializing: initializeSttSessions(language)
    Initializing: createSTT(provider) x2  (Me + Them in parallel)

    Initializing --> RetryInit: throws
    RetryInit: listenService retries up to 10x @ 300ms
    RetryInit --> Initializing: attempt under 10
    RetryInit --> Failed: attempts exhausted

    Initializing --> Active: both sessions open

    state Active {
        [*] --> Listening
        Listening --> Listening: audio chunk every 100ms
        Listening --> Buffering: interim/partial transcript to UI
        Buffering --> Listening: 2s debounce flush, final, persist to DB

        Listening --> KeepAlive: every 60s (OpenAI only)
        KeepAlive --> Listening

        Listening --> Renewing: every 20 min (SESSION_RENEW_INTERVAL_MS)
        Renewing: spawn fresh sessions, 2s overlap, close old
        Renewing --> Listening: hand-off, no audio dropped
    }

    Active --> Dropped: socket onerror/onclose
    Dropped: ONLY logged — no reconnect, no model switch
    Dropped --> Active: requires manual Stop then Listen

    Active --> Closed: Stop / app quit
    Closed: closeSessions() — clear timers, kill SystemAudioDump
    Closed --> [*]
    Failed --> [*]
